snippet: Gov. Bill Walker said he would unilaterally accept federal funds to cover more low-income residents under the program.
abstract: Alaska Gov Bill Walker announces plan to unilaterally expand Medicaid by accepting federal funds that will cover roughly 42,000 Alaskans projected to be eligible under expansion; move comes after state Legislature fails to expand coverage, option for every state under Affordable Care Act.
lead_paragraph: Gov. Bill Walker said he would unilaterally accept federal funds to cover more low-income residents under the program.

headline.main: Over Objections of Legislature, Alaska’s Governor Says He Will Expand Medicaid
